Marking and restrictions on the movement and dispatch and disposal of vaccinated mallard ducks
Portugal shall ensure that vaccinated mallard ducks on the holding referred to in Article 1(1) are:
(a) marked individually;
(b) not moved to other poultry holdings within Portugal;
(c) not dispatched from Portugal.
After their reproductive period, those mallard ducks shall be killed on the holding referred to in Article 1(1) of this Decision in accordance with the requirements of Article 18 of Regulation (EC) No 1099/2009, and their carcases safely shall be disposed of in accordance with the requirements of Regulation (EU) No 142/2011.
